{"type":"message","id":"6459c5a3","parentId":"ab0cbbdd","timestamp":"2026-05-10T14:00:47.745Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the full picture. Let me analyze:\n\n**Standalone workspaces in `/home/halei/`:**\n- `workspace-tts/` → Agent tts workspace\n- `workspace-agent-orchestrator/` → Agent orchestrator workspace\n- `workspace-content/` → Agent content workspace\n- `workspace-director/` → Agent director workspace\n- `workspace-finance/` → Agent finance workspace\n- `workspace-koc/` → Agent koc workspace\n- `workspace-ops/` → Agent ops workspace\n- `workspace-review/` → Agent review workspace\n- `workspace-traffic/` → Agent traffic workspace\n\n**In `.openclaw/workspace/`:**\n- Main workspace (KIIT/main) with files like AGENTS.md, MEMORY.md, SOUL.md etc.\n\n\n- Also contains subdirectories for agents, skills, and various temporary and configuration directories\n\nI notice there's significant duplication: `.openclaw/workspace/` contains workspace-tts, workspace-main, and workspace-selector, while the home directory has all the standalone workspaces plus those same three. So workspace-tts appears in both locations, workspace-main appears in both, and workspace-selector is in `.openclaw/workspace/` but not in the home directory's standalone workspaces.\n\nThe actual independent workspaces are the eight listed: tts, agent-orchestrator, content, director, finance, koc, ops, review, and traffic. The three in `.openclaw/workspace/` (workspace-tts, workspace-main, workspace-selector) seem to be older or redundant versions. The GitHub backup should target the independent workspaces in the home directory, not the ones nested in the openclaw directory.\n","thinkingSignature":"e462a92b589ca128cfe154acd36e7c03e89e3e3012d6e590cb4c7e7768d3a2b9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ikbsholes6qz_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /home/halei/workspace-tts/ && echo \"---\" && cat /home/halei/.openclaw/workspace/.g