{"type":"message","id":"37048be9","parentId":"406ecfef","timestamp":"2026-05-10T14:01:35.770Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the picture clearly:\n\n1. All workspace-* directories are Git repos (but no remotes configured except the old workspace-tts which had the backup repo)\n2. The main workspace at `/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace/` has a git remote pointing to `https://github.com/59330857/openclaw-backup.git` on branch `main`\n3. workspace-tts also has a remote pointing to the same repo\n\nThe user says the data structure changed - all agents now have their own independent workspaces. So the backup scheme needs to change to:\n- Each workspace-* gets its own repo (or all under one repo with different paths?)\n\nThe user said \"千万注意\" (be very careful) - they're worried I'll back up the wrong things.\n\nLet me think about what the new scheme should be. Currently:\n- `/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace/` - main workspace (KIIT's), has backup remote to openclaw-backup\n- `/home/halei/workspace-tts` - tts workspace, also has backup remote\n- `/home/halei/workspace-*` - other agent workspaces, no remotes\n\nLooking at the config in openclaw.json:\n- tts → workspace: \"workspace-tts\" (relative to workspace, so likely /home/halei/.openclaw/workspace-tts or just workspace-tts in some root)\n- Wait, the config shows `\"workspace\": \"workspace-tts\"` for tts - this is relative to... where? The agent's own workspace dir?\n- And content has `\"workspace\": \"/home/halei/workspace-content\"` - absolute path\n- koc has `\"workspace\": \"/home/halei/workspace-koc\"` - absolute path\n\nWait actually:\n- tts: `\"workspace\": \"workspace-tts\"` - this is a relative path, likely relative to the openclaw config dir or home\n\n\n- content, koc, traffic, ops, director, finance, review all use absolute paths under /home/halei/\n\nThis is inconsistent. The user mentioned \"都是独立的workspace了\" (all have independent workspaces now), so 